  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "Seeing numbers instead of contact names in WhatsApp usually indicates that WhatsApp is having trouble accessing or syncing with the contacts saved on your phone. Here's a breakdown of the possible causes and how to fix them:\n\n**1. Contact Syncing Issues:**\n\n*   **WhatsApp Doesn't Have Permission to Access Contacts:** This is the most common reason.\n    *   **How to fix it (Android):**\n        *   Go to your phone's **Settings**.\n        *   Find **Apps** (or Applications, App Manager, etc.).\n        *   Find **WhatsApp** in the list.\n        *   Tap on **Permissions**.\n        *   Make sure **Contacts** is toggled **ON**.  If it's already on, try toggling it OFF, wait a few seconds, and toggle it back ON.\n    *   **How to fix it (iOS):**\n        *   Go to your iPhone's **Settings**.\n        *   Scroll down and tap on **Privacy**.\n        *   Tap on **Contacts**.\n        *   Make sure **WhatsApp** is toggled **ON**.\n\n*   **Contacts Not Saved Correctly:** Contacts might not be saved in a way that WhatsApp can recognize.\n    *   **How to fix it:**\n        *   Make sure your contacts are saved with international phone number format (e.g., +1 for the US, +44 for the UK, etc., followed by the full phone number).  Without the country code, WhatsApp might not be able to link the number to the contact.\n        *   Try saving a contact directly through your phone's default Contacts app (not just within WhatsApp).  If you're saving to a Google account, make sure WhatsApp is syncing with that account.\n\n*   **Multiple Accounts or Inconsistent Contact Storage:**  You might have contacts saved in different accounts (e.g., phone memory, SIM card, Google account, iCloud).  WhatsApp might be accessing the wrong account.\n    *   **How to fix it:**\n        *   **Consolidate your contacts:** Try to consolidate all your contacts into one primary account (usually your Google account or iCloud).  Many phones have a \"Merge Contacts\" feature within the Contacts app.\n        *   **Check WhatsApp's account selection:** In WhatsApp, go to **Settings** > **Contacts** (if available - this option is less common now) and make sure it's set to access the correct account.  If you don't see this option, it should default to accessing all contacts on your phone.\n\n*   **Contact Syncing is Disabled (Android):**\n    *   **How to fix it:**\n        *   Go to your phone's **Settings**.\n        *   Find **Accounts** (or Users & Accounts, etc.).\n        *   Tap on the account where your contacts are saved (likely Google).\n        *   Make sure \"Contacts\" syncing is toggled **ON**.  If it's already on, try toggling it OFF, wait a few seconds, and toggle it back ON.\n\n**2. WhatsApp App Issues:**\n\n*   **Outdated WhatsApp Version:** An outdated version of WhatsApp can have bugs that affect contact syncing.\n    *   **How to fix it:**\n        *   Update WhatsApp to the latest version from the Google Play Store (Android) or App Store (iOS).\n\n*   **Corrupted WhatsApp Cache/Data:** Corrupted data can cause various issues.\n    *   **How to fix it (Android):**\n        *   Go to your phone's **Settings**.\n        *   Find **Apps** (or Applications, App Manager, etc.).\n        *   Find **WhatsApp** in the list.\n        *   Tap on **Storage**.\n        *   Tap on **Clear Cache**.\n        *   **Try restarting WhatsApp after clearing the cache.** If that doesn't work, you can also try **Clear Data**, but be aware that this will reset WhatsApp to its default state, and you'll need to re-verify your phone number.\n    *   **iOS:**  There is no direct \"Clear Cache\" option for individual apps on iOS.  You can try offloading the app (which removes the app's data but keeps the app itself) or deleting and reinstalling the app (which removes everything).\n        *   **Offload App (iOS):** Go to **Settings** > **General** > **iPhone Storage** > **WhatsApp** > **Offload App**. After offloading, tap \"Reinstall App\".\n        *   **Delete and Reinstall App (iOS):**  Make sure you have a backup of your chats before deleting and reinstalling WhatsApp.\n\n*   **Restart WhatsApp:** Sometimes a simple restart can fix temporary glitches.\n    *   **How to fix it:** Close WhatsApp completely (don't just minimize it) and then reopen it.\n\n*   **Restart Your Phone:** A phone restart can resolve many minor issues.\n    *   **How to fix it:** Power off your phone completely, wait a few seconds, and then power it back on.\n\n**3. Other Potential Causes:**\n\n*   **Recent Changes to Your Contacts:**  If you recently changed or added contacts, it might take some time for WhatsApp to sync the updates.\n*   **Storage Issues on Your Phone:** If your phone's storage is almost full, it can interfere with app functionality, including contact syncing.\n*   **WhatsApp Server Issues:** Very rarely, the problem might be on WhatsApp's end. If this is the case, there's not much you can do except wait and try again later. Check online to see if other users are reporting similar issues.\n\n**Troubleshooting Steps (in order):**\n\n1.  **Check Contact Permissions:** Verify that WhatsApp has permission to access your contacts.\n2.  **Restart WhatsApp:** Close and reopen the app.\n3.  **Sync Contacts (If Possible):** Look for a \"Refresh\" or \"Sync Contacts\" option within WhatsApp's settings (some versions have this, some don't).  Also, check your phone's account settings and make sure contact syncing is enabled for the relevant account (e.g., Google).\n4.  **Restart Your Phone:** Power cycle your device.\n5.  **Update WhatsApp:** Make sure you have the latest version.\n6.  **Clear WhatsApp Cache (Android):** Clear the app's cache.\n7.  **Consolidate Contacts:** Ensure your contacts are saved correctly and consistently (international format, same account).\n8.  **Clear WhatsApp Data/Reinstall WhatsApp (Android/iOS):** As a last resort, try clearing the app's data (Android) or deleting and reinstalling the app (iOS).  **Back up your chats first!**\n\nIf none of these solutions work, the issue might be more complex and you might need to contact WhatsApp support for assistance.\n",
